{"text":"How do vaccinations work to protect individuals and communities from infectious diseases, and what is herd immunity?","lang":"en","__index_level_0__":16,"answer":"Хронологија immunity is the protection of a community or society from the negative effects of a disease when a substantial number of people are immunized. This can be achieved through the development of a herd immunity, which is the ability of a group of people to provide protection to those who are not immunized, either through the use of antibodies or other immune responses. Vaccination is an important tool for protecting individuals and communities from infectious diseases, as it provides a way to immunize individuals against a specific disease in a relatively non- risky manner. The effect of vaccination on herd immunity is that it can increase the number of people that are protected from a disease, thereby reducing the number of susceptible individuals and preventing the spread of the disease. In addition, vaccination can also help to reduce the risk of adverse events associated with the disease, by reducing the number of people at risk of contracting the disease. Herd immunity is the protection of a community or society from the negative effects of a disease when a substantial number of people are immunized. This can be achieved through the development of a herd immunity, which is the ability of a group of people to provide protection to those who are not immunized, either through the use of antibody or other immune response. Vaccination is an important tool for protecting individuals and community from infectious disease, as it provides a way to immunate individuals against a specific disease in a relatively non- risky manner. The effect of vaccination on herd immunity is that it can increase the number of people that are protected from a disease, thereby reducing the number of susceptible individuals and preventing the spread of the disease. In addition, vaccination can also help to reduce the risk of adverse event associated with the disease, by reducing the number of people at risk of contracting the disease. The importance of herd immunity lies in its ability to protect individuals and communities from the negative impact of infectious diseases, by providing protection to those who may be unable to respond to vaccination due to age, medical condition, or other factors. Herd immunity can also help to prevent the spread of disease, by reducing the number of susceptible individuals and limiting the number of people that are exposed to the disease. The concept of herd immunity is based on the idea that a group of people must be protected from a disease to ensure that the disease does not spread and affect a larger population. This is because the protection of a group of people through vaccination can provide protection to those who may be unable to respond to vaccination, such as infants, pregnant women, or individuals with weak immune systems. The importance of herd immunity lies in its ability to protect individuals and community from the negative impact of infectious disease, by providing protection to those who may be unable to respond to vaccination due to age, medical condition, or other factor. Herd immunity can also help to prevent the spread of disease, by reducing the number of susceptible individuals and limiting the number of people that are exposed to the disease. The concept of herd immunity is based on the idea that a group of people must be protected from a disease to ensure that the disease does not spread and affect a larger population. This is because the protection of a group of people through vaccination can provide protection to those who may be unable to respond to vaccination, such as infants, pregnant women, or individuals with weak immune system. The concept of herd immunity is based on the idea that a group of people must be protected from a disease to ensure that the disease does not spread and affect a larger population. Th