{"text":"Explain the process of natural selection and how it contributes to the evolution and adaptation of species.","lang":"en","__index_level_0__":19,"answer":"Хронологија\nNatural selection is a process that occurs in the evolution of species, whereby organisms are selected for survival and reproduction based on their ability to withstand the environment. This process is driven by the fact that organisms are not able to survive and reproduce indefinitely, as they are subject to environmental factors such as predation, competition, and mutation.\nThe process of natural selection was first described by Charles Darwin, who observed that all species of life are subject to the same process of selection. The process of selection is a result of the interaction between the environment and the genetic makeup of the organism, which results in the survival and reproduction of certain individuals over others.\nIn order to understand the process of natural selection, it is important to first explain the concept of heredity. Heredity is the idea that the characteristics features of an organism are determined by its genetic makeup, which is the result of the interaction among the genetic, environmental, and developmental factors.\nThe process of selection is a result of the interaction among these factors, as the environment causes the organism to experience various environmental factors, which in \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n