y the movement of the Earth's orbit, which is approximately one orbit every 2 years. Therefore, if we were to measure the movement of the sun in relation to the movement of the Earth's orbit, we could determine that the Earth's orbit is constantly being revised.\nTherefore, the answer to the question of when the Earth orbites the sun is that it's constantly orbiting the sun. The movement of the Earth's orbit around the sun is constantly changing due to the movement of the Earth's rotation and the movement of the sun's movement. Therefore, there is no definitive answer to the question of when the Earth orbites the sun, as the movement of the Earth's orbit is constantly being revised.","model_type":"th_0_selected_LRP_kur_res_zh_zscore|open_ended"}
