{"text":"Những khác biệt chính giữa ngôn ngữ lập trình Python và JavaScript là gì?","lang":"vi","__index_level_0__":2,"answer":"Хронологија thời ơ âm hư củ âm hư Python và JavaScript là gì.\n\nPython là một ngông ngữ lập trình, which means it's a programming language that is based on the idea of using a series of commands to make a computer perform tasks. These commands are called \"functions, and they are used to create a wide range of applications.\n\nJavaScript is a programming language that is similar to Python in that it's based on the idea of using a series of commands to make a computer perform tasks. However, instead of being based on a series of functions, JavaScript is based on a series of \"code-based instructions. These instructions are used to create application, and they can be used to create a wide range of application.\n\nThe main difference between Python and JavaScript is the way that they are used. Python is typically used for more complex applications, such as web development, data analysis, and machine learning. JavaScript is typically used for more practical application, such as web development, data analysis, and machine learning.\n\nPython is also known for its \"linear nature, meaning that it's easy to predict the behavior of a Python program once you know the code that was used to create it. This makes Python a very predictable programming language, which can be useful when working with more complex application.\n\nJavaScript is also known for its \"non-linear nature, meaning that it's difficult to predict the behavior of a JavaScript program once you know the code that was used to create it. This makes JavaScript an unpredictable programming language, which can be frustrating when working with more practical application.\n\nOverall, the main differences between Python and JavaScript are the way that they are used, the way that they are used, and the way that they are used. These differences make Python a more predictable programming language, while making JavaScript an unpredictable programming language.","model_type":"th_0_selected_LRP_kur_res_zh_zscore|open_ended"}
